        },
        "body": "### Summary\r\nThe main fix is removing the incorrect `expiresIn` option from `jwt.verify()`.  \r\n`expiresIn` is only valid during token signing, not verification.\r\n\r\n### Additional improvements\r\n- Added proper handling for invalid/expired tokens (401 instead of server error)\r\n- Added basic \"Bearer <token>\" header validation\r\n- Returned consistent JSON error responses\r\n",
